[gd_scene load_steps=4 format=3 uid="uid://btuxbldf03"]

; Roof piece. 2m x 2m sloped slab — a 0.3m-thick board rotated ~22.5°
; around the X axis so one edge sits flush with the wall-top of a 2.5m
; wall and the other rakes upward, giving the simplest survival-style
; shed roof. Tilted up so the back edge is the high one; pair four of
; them at 90° rotations to roof a 2x2 cabin. Layer 1 collision.
;
; Transform math: Basis(Vector3(1,0,0), 0.3927) — 22.5° in radians; the
; values 0.9238795 / 0.3826834 = cos/sin(22.5°). Origin lives at the
; mid-base so a placement at a wall-top corner snaps cleanly.

